column15: review_text

A lovely place to spend some time, either alone, with friends or with family. The park is actually quite a long stretch, but we only managed to cover the bit around McDonald's.
There's a playground on a sandy stretch just before the sea, there's walking and cycling paths, and even a little wooded marsh area to explore. There's open fields where you can play ball and even fly kites!
Perhaps we were there on a public holiday, but there were many people out enjoying the sunny weather.
If you go on a weekday, I'm sure it will be quieter, and it's definitely a great place to relax and recharge yourself.

Good place for family's outing. Plentiful of playground suitable for young to older kids. Has a Very big field for kite flying. Can enjoy the morning or evening walk as the landscape is beautiful, especially the trees. Honestly, night strolling after dinner is nice too.

You will surprised to see many children still playing at the playground before 8.30pm. There's a beach volleyball court and camping ground. If you're feeling hungry, there's a 24hrs Macdonald. Along the coast line, you can enjoy different scenery.

Came by for a walk and to clock steps on a Sunday afternoon since we haven‚Äôt been here for awhile now.

üö∂üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏?üö∂üèª‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏?was a pretty short walk from end to end overall, with multiple picnic goers spotted, especially near the coast where you can see yacht and small ferries docking by the marina.

There‚Äôs also a bike rental shop at the end of the park, for those looking to get on two wheels üö¥

MacDonald is definitely the go to after a hot day in the park, for either drinks or ice cream treat üòä

Nicely maintained park with marsh garden and also kite flying area. A good trip would start with Mac, and then exploring the greens with also occasional kite watching. Easy parking and usually peaceful to be there, compared to East Coast park.

Recently joined a kite festival event at the West Coast Park and it was truly an immense experience.
Overall the park is very open and you can spend peaceful and quality time here with your friends and families.
You can bring your own food as well.

A lovely park with amenities for kids of all ages. Multiple playgrounds, flying foxes and a maccas right there for a nice meal/breakie.

Would suggest to go early in the morning to beat the crowd and definitely the heat if u have little young ones.

Otherwise an amazing place for kids and adults alike. Haven‚Äôt tried the water yet but will do so the next time.

It's a beautiful park by the coast. A perfect park for an entire family. At one end of the park they have a bikes for hire, and as the park is filled with trees and the path is smooth, the ride around the path is pleasant. The bike paths aren't too busy too so it's a very easy ride, especially for those who want to get back to biking after ages. The park, however, is busy closer the play structures. Lots of families with kids were seen over the weekend. the play structures are so beautifully designed and sectioned away based on age. Playground floors are either rubberized or sanded. Play structures are well maintained too. Restrooms are close by, are so is a vending machine and McDonald's. The park has also space for flying kites, so thats another thing to do. There are exercise contraption for elders to work out too. Overall a beautiful park to spend the day outdoors with family. Carrying lots of water is highly advisable to keep yourself hydrated. Highly recommend.

My first visit to WCP. It has a marsh garden, beach ball pitch, kites flying zone and camping üèï site. It quite big and I only covered the area near to McDonald‚Äôs.  There are a few playgrounds for the young ones. Also the nice place for cycling üö¥‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏? It seems this park has many canon ball trees.

Big park that can accommodate all kinds of interests. I have seen kids, family, couples, runners, meditators, hikers, to be photographers etc etc. a place for everyone. Enjoy the sunset here if the clear sky allows to. I felt the manual constructions of ports and terminals are hinders to natural view. Lot of options for kids to play. Beach volleyball, kite flying place is available. There is also a dedicated place for setting up tents.
Nice park with nature and in front of the beach. Lots of playgrounds (around 4). But a little bit more for small kids. Bigger ones risk to be annoyed...  there's a mc do inside the park too.

A nice park though not the greatest in Singapore. Mainly due to the beach as you see a lot of cargo ships. Other than this, it has the usual amenities like children‚Äôs playground, fitness areas and a cafe (McDonald‚Äôs). There is also a bicycle rental shop. Parking tends to be limited if you want to park at the carpark nearest to McDonald‚Äôs.  The park can be said is divided into two parts with an underpass linking both. The western part where McDonald‚Äôs is located has the most activities and most of the features are found there.

This amazing big park has so much to offer, from plenty of play structures to explore. Our favorite was the flying fox as not every outdoor playground has it. There‚Äôs a sandpit area as well that offers tons of fun and imagination for your little ones. And the park is a pram friendly walk, just like most of the places here in Singapore. And if you feel hungry, there‚Äôs a McDonalds nearby. Definitely will come back again and will try to be as early as possible! Because it‚Äôs starting to get busy as early as 10am. Just love the place!

The Park has big open ground and greenery suitable to host cultural events or festive activities. There is McDonald‚Äôs at car park 3. There are children playgrounds and activity areas, some shaded seating / pergolas restrooms. Great for picnic and relaxing with family or cycling. We went their to celebrate the Kite Flying festival as part of Makar Sankranti or Uttarayan Festival. It was great experience after so many years. Could not do it for past dew years sue to COVID. All in all great place to spend time with family and kids.

Normal place to bring the kiddos, great for picnic. Nearby macdonald, one can also rent bikes which is now a plus point, this is a pretty new addition.
Comes w beach volleyball Court. Most of the playgrounds are sand type so do wear slippers if u don't not want the shoes to be filled with sands.
Comes w parking lots, however, not free üòÖ

Perfect place to watch the sunset. If you‚Äôre lucky you get to see some flying fishes. Hungry? Head down to the MacDonald‚Äôs nearby. My favourite park. Bring to your kids to the many playground attractions here.

4 Stars for this Park.
West Coast Park has 2 parts to it.
According to the map, the part where the fountain is not well maintained. The paths at certain parts are with algae and grass. It can be very slippery.
They have Dog Run area, Bathing area for $10 for 10 minutes, and you can rent  bicycles there. Quite a few wild rooster and hen family. I managed to see a family of 4 Mother hen with 3 little chicks.
The more developed part of the part is nearer to Sea. You can enjoy the sea view and sea breeze. There are lots of different  playgrounds for children over there. Best of all, you can have your meals at Macdonalds after that which is nearby.
Beautiful park, though It can get overcrowded during weekends and school holidays.  You would b able to spot gorgeous special breed of birds .. sometimes you can spot cheeky monkeys and otters too ..

Well laid Out urban park, with quaint board walks nestled  in the western corner of lush greenery.
Many kiddy play areas and of course the mandatory open spaces for field sports. Something for everyone. I hear that with proper permissions tenting and camping are allowed too! ( check out the NParks website)
A cycle rental place of the cherry on top. Could have done without the McDonald‚Äôs thoughüòé, would have preferred a good old kopitiam with fruit and juice options and other traditional singaporean favourites

Much smaller than the East Coast Park, this one has the advantage of being less crowded. Just about fine for a quick & short walk, but not if u r keen for a long jig or walk with beautiful views of the sea. In fact, the construction activity actually spoils the view of the sunset. We were lucky to hav the cloud cover after a short shower playing with colours in the sky.
a very big and clean park, you can camp there but don't make campfires or barbecue there. there is fishing, animals like otters or large lizards are released and swim freely
One of the best spot to catch sunset in the west. The sun can be as big as it gets here if you are lucky!

Nice park for a walk or run or even for a short camping trip.
There are options for renting a bicycle as well and benches are arranged along the coast, facing the water from Singapore Strait.
Love doing my night walks here after work. Safe even when i go there alone and the park is free of garbage. Peaceful and relaxing as it is abundant of trees and plants. Feel so close to nature.
Went last Friday for cycling, place is clean and green. Saw quite many cute squirrels and a üêç üò¨
Nice park to hang out with family. Leisure afternoon cycling around, had fun at the playground, and muched at McD

The seaside park in the west is much smaller than the east coast one. Although there are playgrounds, the planning is rather chaotic.  There are not many places to eat around, McDonald's is one of them.  Many children are learning roller skating.  If you get there by bus, there will be many large trucks on the road and you need to pay attention to your safety.  In comparison, I still prefer East Coast Park.
Ridden my gravel bike at the West Coast Park during a weekend. Due to its size and years of  development, you can always find a quiet and green environment for your relaxation in this park.
Nice big park. Great for outdoor group and family activities. I got stuck in the carpark and couldn't get out but that's probably on me. Don't be like me. Have a working pass to pay for parking.
Absolutely lovely park for nature, camping, sports and sea
Really nice park with volleyball spots as well great for baseball or football. Dog lovers must see this park as there is special place to play.
Wonderful place to spend your evenings either in solitude or with family and friends.

A nice cosy park in the west side of Singapore, you can come here to chill and stroll with family and friends. This park is clean and well maintained, pavements are suitable for running, cycling, skateboarding and all sorts of activities. The beach is located towards the western stretch where you can appreciate the urban landscape of nearby industrial structures and yachts some distance away.
Nice place for cycling.  Except that there are many pedestrians who likes to walk in middle of road .. risking both pedestrians and cyclists and roller bladers .
Great place for joging, running, bicycling, and what ever comes to mind.
Quiet place for hang out and walking . Not as much as people as compare to East Coast park

Large space for kids and adults to have fun. The highlight is probably the spider web climb to the top (about 3 storeys high) with 2 slides in the middle, and also the 4 flying fox lanes that can allow you to slide from one end to the other, suspended on a metal cable, sitted on a rubber seat. Has a nice beach and sandy areas for play. Many kite flyers on a windy day too. Only place to eat is a McDonald‚Äôs there at the park with even a drive thru.

A great place to spend an afternoon at. I was there usually to fly kite or bring my dog to the dog run park.

Unfortunately there is only MacDonald's at the park. Not easy to go by public transport as I see most people drive there.

A breezy park for great walk and family outing. Beautiful harbour views captured with my handphone and a family enjoying cycling along the paths. Everywhere are the big trees shading with natural feelings!

Each round is about 5km. Ran 2 rounds and had enjoyed the sea breeze and trees shielding me from the scorching sun.

Wonderful place to bring family for picnic, cycling, strolling, fishing, bird sighting etc.

There's also a McDonald at carpark 3!

Has several playgrounds for kids of all ages, peaceful clean huge space for public. Only peeve is it doesn't have variety of food options except a huge macdonalds around and limited shelter in the event of sudden wet weather.

Great for picnic. Nothing much for fishing. Many people bring tent to chill there. Two parts, one side more greeny, for dog walk. Another part more family based, with playground, sports field, sand, beach and all. Mcdonalds is the only eatery.

It's one of my favourite parks in Singapore.

From seaside ‚õ±Ô∏è walks üö∂‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏?with views of the port and marina to the large playing fields, beach volleyball üèê courts to walking üö∂‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏?and cycling üö≤ trails üë£ West Coast Park extends over a good portion of Singapore Island's West Coast skirting around Port activities, housing and university buildings.

The park also hosts several large playgrounds, fitness areas , gardens, and a lake. Also, several toilets üöª, water fountains ‚õ≤Ô∏è, a dog washing station, and also a branch of McDonald's.

There are also barbecue pits for hire as well as bicycles üö≤ to explore the full extent of the park.

Honestly, I could not think of what more this park could offer. Perhaps more wet weather options as there are no real sheltered options in rain or thunder, but who wants to go to the park in the rain? You can always hang out at McDonald's until it clears up!

Oh, how to sing praises for this lovely, lovely park!
In these uncertain days with Covid-19 health scare, this park is literally the life savior to my whole family!!
The vast space, those eye - soothing greenary, the squirrels darting around the trees... the occasional birds that one can see perching on tree tops... all the fitness equipment provided in various spots in the park (though I have not used those for the past months since March because of my fear of catching germs üòÖ) are but a few attractions of this lovely place for me.
However... the icing on the cake... is la Mer!  üåä üåä üåä üåä üåä

Just gazing at the waves breaking upon the sands down the slope at the water edge is Nirvana for me. In the evening, looking at the sun setting behind the horizon painting the skies with red and gold, the last rays of the sun for the day shimmering on the sea surface turning it into liquid gold... how can one rate such beautiful sights by a simple Star rating system?

Visit this park. You will have health benefits by taking a walk or jogging.
The well kept rest rooms, the wending machines to get a refreshing drink, bicycle s and some other riding machines one can rent for a reasonable price, the BBQ pits (though they are out of bounds at present as it should be), are  some of the great amenities this place provides. You will feel happier when you visit the park than you were before doing so, I can wholeheartedly assure!
Fave goto park for quiet contemplation and exercise on weekday mornings

You can see a lot of the container ships as this place is close to one of the world busiest port. There are a few play ground. Good for family with kids and there is a McDonald restaurant in the park.

Very nice place to watch sunset. There is also bike rental. Park is not big, you can finish cycling in 1h30min. Carpark is not free even on sunday. Didnt manage to find any nearby free place to park. Sea is deep and slippery on the breakwater wall. Be careful if you have small children.
We went there for our morning walk, the park was spacious and quite empty on a Friday morning. There is a walking trail (just beside a wharf) that leads into a mangrove swamp.
One of the bigger parks in the West part of Singapore, the usual place where I will stop for break while cycling around Singapore.  Quiet location as well.  Serene and peaceful
The park is very well maintained. Good for cycling n jogging. There is an interesting natural trail across Sungei Kechil Pandan which has families of otters n `4 legged Snake`

Weekends are for early morning runs and exploring places. And West coast park has it all, from beautiful gardens to clear coastline üòå. One can easily spent a few hours relaxing, getting to know the place and enjoying the views.

It is an amazing place to spend a day out for some family fun. A huge park for jogging, a beautiful view with lots of greenery and with a waterfront. Not busy on a weekday, making it quite a private day out on a weekday. Several playgrounds catering to a wide age range: 2-12year old. Even my 1 year old enjoyed it. There is a free public toilet which is pretty clean.
McDonald's strategically place a restaurant (opened 24 hours drive through) here with a normal restaurant, roofed outdoor seats, and a separate air-conditioned annex, presumably for party reservations (we were on a school outing and had the annex all to ourselves. On another note, it would be nice if there were some variety and choice other than McD. But given that there are few buildings in this park (a rare sight in Singapore), sticking to only one restaurant may not be such a bad thing.
A gem in the west of Singapore!
(Please give a thumbs up if this review is useful. Thanks!)
West Coast parkrun ... great location, lovely team, as ever, a brilliant parkrun

West Coast Park is a great park for kids. There are many playgrounds for kids and it‚Äôs massive. You can ride a bike or play a kite in the park (bring your own bike üö≤/ kite). Don‚Äôt forget your picnic mat if you want to enjoy the sunbathing! Lovely park!!

Popular with joggers, cyclists, dog owners and families, this locale offers a one stop solution for getting involved in some outdoor activities. It‚Äôs well catered for various activities, such as large open field for kite flying, a beach Volleyball court, children play areas, camp grounds, BBQ facilities and fishing jetty. Numerous benches are spread around, with quite a few under shade. A good amount of parking spaces are made available situated along side the length of the park. It appears to be quite a popular place to go, and deserves a visit. Only downturn, the seaside view is not going the most picturesque, and certainly won‚Äôt be gracing the covers of aspirational travel destination magazines any time soon

West Coast Park is a peaceful place with large yards to play volleyball, fly kites, work out, you name it. Also, having the harbor, even seaport, taking more natural pictures, and visitors can rent bikes to explore full park. Overall, it's fresh view.

This park is filled with all types of scenery... in these photos you see boats, container cranes and a receding shoreline during a low tide. Always a favorite park and site to visit. Get a workout, soak in some fresh air, enjoy the view.

Our favourite park to bring the children.. they have several playgrounds for the children of varying ages, with a sandpit playground for the youngest group with a set of swings and a Viking ship shaped slide. Toddlers will be kept entertained with a larger playground next to it with roundabouts, slides and more swings. Older kids will love the other playground which comes with a very high climbing structure with slides, flying foxes and other activities.

This is a perfect park for a good getaway from your routine life. With all the lush greenery, walkways, cycling tracks, sea shore, ships and containers, and ofcourse the fresh air can rejuvenate anybody. A must visit place!

Good:

1. Decent park next door.
2.  Not very crowded.
3. Good connectivity through bus 175, 176.
4. Has a dog run, bar-b-q pits, cycle rentals.
5. Tracks are smooth enough for skating.
6. Promenade providing views of port, good sunset.
7. 24/7 McDonald's to carb up.
8. Decent parking.
9. Cleaner compared to east coast park.
10. Decent kids playing area.
11. Big open area for matches, social functions.
12. Permanent stage for various activities.

Bad:

1. No connectivity by MRT.
2. Very small coastline.
3. No other eating joint except McDonald's.
4. Very few working water fountains.
5. Rodents, cockroaches seen @promenade.

It is truly adventurous hiking/exercising to spot some squirrels and a venom Spitting cobra. A coastal beach habitat and mangrove swamp can be found here as well. I am glad that there is good offers found in McDonald's to eat breakfast or supper.

One of my favourite weekend spot to relax and exercise. This place has undergone many changes since I've first came here more than 2 decades ago. Recently the McDonald's is going through a bit of renovation as well.

There's a dog playground and many bbq areas. Somewhere near it there's also an archery workshop, looks quite interesting. However 1 sad thing is part of this park is blocked by a harbour where a lot of cargos will block your view from the sea.
A beautiful park definitely for families to relax and jogging experience there was amazing with seaside views and fresh air

NParks had done it's best. The natives are the downers.  From one angle, the place looks like a refugee camp with tents all over. From another it was Pasir Panjang of the 1960s complete with boatmen, sampans, rod fishermen and flotsam at the water edge.

Yet there is the recently renovated Macdonald's, scruffy yachts and glistening condos dotting the skyline.

For me the draw is the seafront walk, super cycling tracks and huge carpark- as long as the tour coaches aren't there.

Be warned, put on lots of mosquito repellant when venturing into the "forest" swamps. Or just stay in the open.
It is big park with good sea view. Nice place for tent stay and children playing.
Nice big park with lots of children playground. We were there on a Sunday morning and there was a soccer clinic ongoing for the kids. Carpark was plentiful except for the section near Macdonald's.

A great place for evening run with shades of evening sky, and the sea water on rocks coastal line has calming effect after a long day of work. You could bring your family and kids, friends and beloved for sports games such as volley ball, frisbee, kite flying, soccer, running, pokemoning, harry pottering, cycling, phototaking, camping, bbqing, playground fun, etc.

The "sister" park of the famous East Coast Park (ECP) but often perceived as less glamorous or smaller, West Coast Park (WCP) is a public park located ight beside the Pasir Panjang Terminal and West Coast Highway.

While doesn't get as much attention as other parks in Singapore like Bishan AMK, ECP or Botanic Gardens, WCP is still uniquely special.
The park is divided into two sections and located on the eastern side, you can find probably the biggest dog run in Singapore, even bigger than ECP's! You don't have to worry about the issue of crowding here as compared to Bishan AMK for example, as there is ample space available. There is also a concrete pavement that connects the two ends of the dog run together, with shaded seatings and table areas. Best of all, there's even a dog wash machine near the carpark for you to rinse off after a long day of fun.

Dog run aside, the Eastern part of WCP is also more rustic and "wild". Numerous big trees cover the paths with their stretched canopies and if you're feeling adventurous, you can also go off the beaten track through pebble paths that cut into the vegetation.

The Western side of the park on the other hand is more curated and "civilised", with playgrounds and amenities like McDonald's. You can also view the sea there!

It was quite a pleasant surprise for us when we visited, and despite it being a Saturday morning the crowd was lesser than expected. The hooman also managed to capture many pawsome pictures during our morning there. It was definitely an enjoyable experience and if you're staying in the west, West Coast Park is definitely worth a visit!

This is a good sized park with plenty of paved, smooth surface trails for hiking, walking, running or bicycling. Many tall trees with huge spreading canopies of lush green leaves. People come here to exercise or walk their dogs or just relax.
If you have any engineering minds in the family it is also fun to walk along the path that fronts the port so you can see the container lifter/sorter/loading action going on. All those giant metal containers from around the world converge here and can be viewed as you walk.
Notes: I love this park on a hot sunny day or in the evening too. They do have a restroom and a foot rinsing station if you need it. As of August 2018 the dog washing booth is closed for renovations. A vending machine near restoom has beverages for $1 to $1.50.

A park while not as large as east coast park, still offers a great experience whether you are just having a casual stroll, or running/cycling laps. Even learn how to roller blade here.

The children‚Äôs obstacle course is very good in training agility and motor skills.

There is a macdonalds nearby which is not your typical neighbourhood outlet.

But the afternoon sun or rain might be a pain as shelter is limited here.
This park is calm and beautiful. One should visit for it's abundant space for leisure activities and an amazing Marsh garden. I would recommend to visit on weekdays to enjoy without crowds.
Nice Park with seaside view of shipyard. Not so much for tourist mainly locals. Garden not as mature but good job done by national parks as always. Tiger Orchid was in bloom when I visited today.
Nice place to walk. Should visit if you have not. But do visit in the morning or evening when it is cooler and shady.

Great park. Lots of parking. Trees around for shade and when all else fails, McDonalds in nearby. There are heaps of various activities for kids of all ages. Good footpaths around so it's easy to travel. I would advise alot of water as it can get really humid and hot. Watch out for bicycles.

If you are lucky you might get to see the resident who has 2 blue Macau's. Amazing things.

Nice place for picnic üß∫ there are many people in the park too (jogging, having a picnic, playing soccer, beach volleyball etc).

Come here to catch a nice sunset!! Easily accessible from Clementi interchange (bus 175). Macs can get a little crowded.

Nice park to walk, jog or chill out. Its by the sea with many big green grass patches to do your activities. Have few playground for kids to play and fitness corners as well. There is also a MacDonald‚Äôs located within the park that has drive thru.

One of our favorite park for bring my son and pet to play and spend time on weekend! They will have may others kids so they will playing each other and interaction. Just the women toilet a bit dirty and smelly (yeah understand for outdoor toilet). You need bring some beach mat and pack your food and will be more fun!

Nice park with wide green park, few kids playgrounds, artificial sands, plenty of high trees.
Crowded during weekends with lot family picnic and enjoying time.
Have one and only McDonald's 24 hours MC Cafe too.
Great for couples and friends hanging around at late night.
Nearby port with lot of vessels and varies ships, cranes, etc.
Morning and evening jogging will be very fun. Otherwise cycling or skating would be nice either.
Open field however is very hot during noon.
Too bad, no others restaurant or food court nearby.
Plenty of carpark but seems no near to MRT.

If you have a kid, don‚Äôt miss to visit this amazing big park. So much to offer, from plenty of play structures to explore. Our favorite was the flying fox as not every outdoor playground has it. There‚Äôs a sandpit area as well that offers tons of fun and imagination for your little ones. And the park is a pram friendly walk, just like most of the places here in Singapore. And if you feel hungry, there‚Äôs a McDonalds nearby. Definitely will come back again and will try to be as early as possible! Because it‚Äôs starting to get busy as early as 10am. Just love the place! Perfect for the family weekend.

There's something for everyone here.

Have a dog? Then bring her to the dog park and let her loose. There's a dog wash at carpark 1 with a public washroom and plenty of space to run about.

Have kids? Then there's playground and adventure park with sand, swing and open field for flying kites. Located just behind McDonald's.

Love nature? You can camp overnight, go to the mangrove area where birds are and even spot monkeys, squirrels around the park.

Love BBQ? There's a couple of BBQ pits for that class gathering.

Love cycling? There's a bike rental with all sorts of unique bikes for couples and family. And a bike course in the park.
great park for jogging and cycling in west coast area, many bird and squirrel, they have many facilities such camp area, kids outbond, beach volley ball, dog run area, fishing
Amazing place to hang out with your family, friend and loved one. Its free just bring insect repellant lotions.
Nice park with huge playground and open space for kite flying. Good view of the harbour. Good for the young and energetic.
Small, quiet and green park; good for sunset/ sunrise view and exercising

big patch of grass for picnic and sports, beach volleyball/ tennis or even cycle around the park. alternatively, can sit and chill while looking at the water, sunset and ferries. there‚Äôs also a huge playground for the kids. just a great place for families and friends all day.
Lovely park. Love the raintrees and cycling routes here. There is actually an underpass that connects to the other side of the park.  Would come back to enjoy the scenery, serenity and nature.

Good spread of activities although few dining choices. There is a McDonald's in the park near the children's playground. Not as many slides as one would find in Admiralty or the newer playgrounds but the variety is still good and offers a different experience. The park is a long stretch with a big field for sports and a boardwalk which offers nature lovers some respite.
A nice place to chill at. Best part would be the sunset seaview with the boats and ships.
Can get quite hot along the boardwalk due to lack of trees, best to come early sunrise or between 630-8pm. A lot less crowded than ECP

A park built on reclaimed land between Pasir Panjang Port and West Coast. Has almost every facility a park needs but none outstanding.

A MacDonald‚Äôs is conveniently built at the west end of the park
Very clean and green place. Quiet and serene. Not crowded too.
Nice place to stroll and relax. Few playground for kids and places for sight seeing. Also there are bicycle kiosk if you decide to cycle. Overall its a good area to adventure with friends and family.

The wind was just nice that day. Me and my buddy had a sip on the blackest coffee macdonalds had to offer.

Waiting for time to fly, we sat on the coast looking straight to the parking boats at the sea.

A sudden pause happened. I looked in his eyes. He looked through me. His face changed to something suspicious. We exchanged looks for a moment and i had to break the news to him.

I said " i farted bro. Paiseh"
very peaceful place to walk at, alone, with family or friends and pets too!!!
I love the different kind of Asian cuisines and the ambiance plus the cozy park for kidsüá∏üá¨

Nice park to visit, especially you need some quite time, just walk around with the beautiful scene, n let your heart speaküíì, hear from the inner voice, n let your minds be peaceful ‚ò?,https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOjggP6dzNxhTVdso04wyPLp6bEPSnNYSXhBDPI,https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOjggP6dzNxhTVdso04wyPLp6bEPSnNYSXhBDPI
Very relaxing with great view of the port and natural.
After a long time since sec sch days. Came here and cycle again great outing small park with McDonald.
Beautiful, quiet and serene, good for family bonding stations like playgrounds, jogging, walking, dog walking, a slew of great quality time to be spent here when the sun isn't so hot
Have always loved this park. What a view of the sea and boats docked at RSYC
Went there early morning not so crowded. Good for cycling and jogging.
Very relaxing , good place for jogging ,cycling , tent area , kids play grounds etc.
There's McDonald's, there's a bicycle shop but they're a little too far apart. There's also sand playgrounds for older and younger children. A good outing location for families.

There are 3 Parks joined Tog. The furthest one can go all the way to Pasir Panjang whole sale market and a short walk to haw par villa.

There is also a dog run, kite area, campsites and playgrounds.

"West Coast Park was developed on a piece of reclaimed land. The park was completed in 1979. There's the Adventure Play Area which is divided into age-specific zones. Each area caters to the activity preferences and levels for its specific age group. The playground in the West Coast Park is one of the largest in Singapore, with play equipment such as a tall rope pyramid and 'flying fox'. Also available are barbecue pits, camping areas, bicycle obstacle course, sand play area and many more. A small, shadeless dog run area has been fenced off at the eastern end of the park, one of only two public places in Singapore where dogs may walk off-leash, and the only such place that is freely accessible. A McDonald's fast-food outlet is located in the western part of the park." - Wikipedia

Themed as the "Play Centre in the West", West Coast Park is a large regional park located in the southwest of Singapore. A linear park comprising 50 hectares of park land, the park runs parallel to West Coast Highway.

Standing at the centre core of Area 3 is the Adventure Play Area that caters to people of different age groups, from toddlers to young adults. This is the heart and most active zone of West Coast Park. If you like a quiet and peaceful environment, the eastern portion at Area 1 would be a good choice for park users to rest and relax. The western portion of the park has been transformed into a haven for park visitors who enjoy challenging and adventurous activities.

What a lovely park!  Great nature trails.  Lots of green areas with lush foliage.  Easy walking.  And wonderful views at the waterfront - especially if there's a visible sunset!  Great playgrounds and dandy areas for kids too.  We loved it!
Get your Mac's here
Great place to bring kid out on weekend
West coast park also clean and nice to walk around that place with the seaside.
No natural air flow since they block the airway when you are doing BBQ in the place and lightings are dim and not bright
Fantastic place for children,  so different types of playgrounds cater for different age groups
Cheap get away from urban landscape
It's nice place for jogging and barbequing

It is a good place for leisure and sports. There are trees and flowers around it, and there is the sea. There are also  children's playground, and there are facilities for parking bicycles. West Coast Park

This is a place where parents can share quality time with their families.  There are so many facilities for kids and adults to enjoy together.  So much open space for the kids to run freely.  There is also a boardwalk that parents can bring kids along and explain to kids how mangrove swamps are all over Singapore coast and there are so much creatures living in those swamp.  There is also a small jetting for fishing too.  This is a place for wholesome activities.  Camping and BBQ facilities are available too.  Last but not least there is a MacDonald in the park.

Another beautiful place to be at especially early mornings but the sunset is even more prettier. There are washrooms and MCDONALD'S at a walking distance and you can jogg, cycle, skate on the long trails available along the coast. No 7/11 available nearby and hence theres no place to buy alcohol.

Fun activities for whole family. Can play in big playground including sandbox, giant climbing area, zip line, can fly kites,  fish, go cycling,  jogging or just have a fun picnic in d green grass with plenty of shade. If hungry got mac donald including a mac cafe in the part itself.
Good place to hang out with family. Only not so much food places. Only 1 mac donld.

A relatively small park but it has Macdonalds and ample parking lots for those who drive. The main attraction for me is the seafront where you can view the yachts and boats, and the background of gantry cranes make the scene rather unique in its way.
Unpredictable weather, went there twice and both of the time it always rains after a short while good if you like to walk under the rain

Less crowded than East Coast Park, and similar nice foot paths and bike paths and bike rentals.   McD is a literal hotspot for rest and snack or meal.  Camping available, and nice to watch kite fliers on the weekend.   Far west side has a board walk along a water way where otters seem to frequent, along with big Lizards.
I like wcp for the dog run - big and sizable enough to allow them to run - real run

Good park to cycle and run.. Not so much people, and has quite a few toilets and vending machines. There is even a Go Central bike rental shop for you to rent bikes to cycle around.. Best part, is that there is a McDonald's and a Mccafe on site! Best place to catch a cuppa n cakes after the exercise! üòÑüö¥üèÉü§∏
I go jogging here quite often. I find quite a few groups actively engaging in sports, kite flying and leisurely picnics as well. Cycling is fun and sitting on the beach is calming too üòä
Good parking space. Got only Mac Donalds if you dont mind. Good Toilet facilities. Nice ambience especially looking at the liner...

Still the best areas to relax and big Mac Donald's in the West. Photos place for study, birthday celebration (kids friendly, staff are friendly too, etc) once done, short stroll in the park. Once done, can still go to west coast plaza or wet market.
Accessibility: 2/5 (nearest mrt Clementi and Take a bus)

The wind is running with cool gentle breeze, caresses her skin as it ruffles her dress.
Again and again.

Great park by the sea. Frequented by people in the neighborhood with families, dogs (leashed), to play soccer, beach volleyball, fly kites, jog or just enjoy the view.

It also boasts a wide variety of playground activities and a popular McDonalds.

My kids love this park. Huge playground for the kids to play. Sandpit, swing and slides area can be quite busy over the weekend. What I really like in this place is that it has shaded areas to hang around if you do not want to be exposed in the sun. It is also convenient to have Mac Donald's in the area.
Sky, water and nature. A good place for evening walk üòÜ
Good place to have a picnic with the family. Many groups made use of the playing field. Yet there's ample room for people to do light exercises and walks. You may catch the otters in the waters...

Nice and quiet alternative to East Coast Park with ample jogging and cycling paths. Has a big field for functions and events with restrooms within walking distance. The golden arch nearby is a haven for thirsty and hungry visitors. Lots of car Park space.

In land scarce Singapore, I do appreciate the fact that we have allocated some space to have outdoor recreational activities. It's certainly not East Coast Beach but hey, for anyone else like me who stays in the western part of Singapore, I am grateful that West Coast Park is an option. Certain areas within the park are cordoned off(social distancing measures) but I am sure this will be lifted once when the situation improves. Bring a kite, cold drinks and propped up a chair or 2. It's good to be out in the open with the family.
Nice and beautiful place to hangout with friends. A must visit for those interested in playing beach volleyball. It has quite few courts and few do not need advance booking.

Relaxing place where u can enjoy a walk thru the park, have fun at the huge playground, enjoy the seaside and there is even a swarm area where you can walk on the boardwalk! Carpark is not free though. Macdonald's carpark is only 1st hour free.
Avoid being fined by taking note:
NO SMOKING EVEN IN THE CARPARK AS IT IS STILL DESIGNATED PART OF THE PARK.
A nice family gathering place.
luxury..spacious..McDonald's..sea
Not many places in singapore these days to have such a view other than changi and East coast park.
Good for exercise. There are two beach volleyball fields, bbq pits and also jogging and biking tracks. The camping ground is closed cos of covid.

Great place to enjoy plenty of activities with families, fur kids and friends. Nice park for morning jog, cycling, roller blading, frisbee, beach ball, kites flying and more. Young children will be spoilt for choice for the wide range of playgrounds there.

Have a sumptuous breakfast and fresh coffee at McDonald before strolling along the coast to feel the breeze and grasp a nice view of the open sea and ships is another great enjoyment to start the day.
Very good location for kids.

Great alternative to ECP that has become so crowded. Notably there are 4 mini ziplines, 2 large climbing nets, and several separate playgrounds with spacious sandpits! The playgrounds cater for kids big and small with 'bucket seat' swings and balance beams to more advance climbing nets.
There's also a public toilet and McDonald's within a short walking distance. Not to mention large open grass covered spaces that are often used for team sports and games facing the water!
Great place for families with children.

A great place for leisure walk, jogging or running amidst beaitiful shrubs, short and tall trees.  Also, a lovely pond at the lower
Level where you can watch different kind of birds as well as butterflies.

Excellent place for family with kids. So many options of playground for kids of all ages and there's enough space for sufficient social distancing.

Big carpark available too so parking shouldn't be an issue. There's a big Macdonald to satisfy all our addiction too.

What I like about this place other than the above is the view of the sea. You can take a relax stroll and view the yatch. Further back there's the VLCC at the port terminal, and beside them are the jack up rigs of PPL.

Pretty empty for a park but maybe it's because I went on a weekday. The open field is a sight to see, quite rare in SG I think. Nice change of environment for cyclists and runners since it's much less crowded than east coast park. Not a lot of food options though only got Mac here and a small mall nearby. Also quite small track to cycle I think it loops for about 5km

Great place to cycle and enjoy the scenic sea. McDonald's' is always packed though so I wouldn't recommend this place to chill. West Coast Park is really great for kids to play with their friends as there are big open spaces for activities.
Great fun playground with lots of play equipment, and the bonus of the huge green areas to run around or play ball on too.  Not 5 stars as the large slides were closed off, I assume for renovations.

A very well maintened park, spread over a vast expanse! The park has many varieties of simple as well as challenging games for kids. It also has great network of nicely paved path. One can smoothly skate over these tracks, do cycling, tricycling or jogging. Eventhough hundreds of people visit this place, it never feels crowded due to its huge area!
Greenery is well maintened. One small portion is dedicated for camping. A very big McDonald's is present for snacking at will.
This park is sea facing, and there's a yacht club nearby. Gives you splendid view of many yachts. Sea breezes  from one side are refreshing, and so is smell of dense greenery from the other side.
A must visit if you are on the west coast. (Certainly not if you are in Singapore for tourism, it will eat up lot of your time) :)
My favourite park. Scenery at the ocean area makes me emotional during blue skies with a big sun.

A great fun, safe place for the kids to play for free. Variety of play areas for different ages to keep the kids busy and entertained. We also enjoy sitting by the nearby coast and watching the boats.
Best place for cycling, jogging, exercise, beach side. Good place for kids to play around.

Cycling, relaxing, drinking beer..this place is awesome for getting away and just relaxing. Gets a little busy in the food places at night but there is so much space you can be on your own too if you want. Forget Chinese gardens. This is the place to come to stretch your legs. Lovely place to spend your leisure times. Wanna go with your family and friends for picnic or barbecue? Also can do it here. Amazing sea view, cycling tracks, quality sea food all are available here.
Quaint massive park compared to its counterpart ECP.  Enjoyed the tranquility and the laidback vibe.
very nice place

Coastal area, no beach, only rocks, an open area where some sports activities can be done here. A joint jogging and biking track that can lead to some secluded area of the park. There are a few good playground and adventure setups in the central area that caters to small children and older kids. Not forgetting a Big M restaurant that is open for 24 hrs.
Nice public park with plenty of space that is ideal for drone flying. . . . good airiel view of Keppel Marina and the PSA docks.

Nice place to go to in good weather. Usually lots of people around even at night. Camping here is fine but can be noisy at night due to kids at the playground, alarms/horns from the shipyard, and music being blasted from e-scooter riders. There's a macs there which offers indoor and outdoor seating.
Great park in the west of singapore. Many playgrounds for kids. Open spaces for dog runs and large open playgrounds for sports and camping.

I love the layout of the park. But do find it a tad too crowded during weekend. Maybe avoid weekends which also happens to be a public holiday. Otherwise, loving it. Will definitely visit it again soon.
Nice place with children playground and camping area.

A very nice place for young and old and family. The park is shady and full of greenery and one can jog there anytime of the day because of the shade provided by the trees. There is a very nice playground for children and there are ample exercise corners with ex equipment for one to exercise. And yes, there is a 24/7 Mac at the park.
Good stop for toilet break and water refill when cycling.

Clean and flat decent floor for jogging. Nice pier both towards the ocean and marsh garden. Hand full of native botanicals and some exotic which attracts cute species. Camping side are decent and no worries of snakes or tall grass (safety wise) BBQ corner are easily access our there's MC Donald's as an option. Children playground and outdoor gym facilities Seems well maintained and safe üòéüëç to keep it short, I can see the effort spent and will highly recommend for a visit.
Had a great time with my kids there. Awesome place for family

Good open spaces with fairly well maintained environment. Place includes bicycle rental, Mc-Donalds and a camping site. Usual facilities like toilets available. Some contruction going on at this time. Not crowded.
Quiet and good place for cycling

Great energy there! Many upgraded children play spaces. Big field with many activities going on. Camping area for families who like to connect with nature. Public shower and toilet facilities. And a MacDonald's

I love this place... better than East coast

Authorities or the carpark operator needs to put a yellow box at the intersection point at the exit of carpark 3 along the road leading into the McDonald's drive-through.

Great place to unwind with your family .

You can play beach volleyball , frisbee, fly kites , indulge in play area for kids ( including sand play ) or just sit and enjoy the lush green park . Great place to see the sun set .

Only flip side is not many eating options in the park except McDonalds .

i came there for a school event and let me tell you i was VERY tempted to run away and play the playgrounds. this park had many playgrounds and i think it's very suitable for kids and teens to hang out and just chill. there is also a McDonald's near here so you can play at the playgrounds before settling down and having a meal. very kid friendly but you have to beware that there is some high structures so you have to be careful incase you slip off. please do not play after it rained or when it is raining as it may be very slippery

Nice location to go with family
And more greenery park and suitable place for childrens

Nice calming location. Great amenities, especially for kiddies. Only down side is the lack of showering facilities. That could come in handy especially after workout, before meeting people at MacDonalds for instance.

One of our favourite places for a weekend outing! It's a beautiful place with the view of the beach,  lots of play areas, and sandplay...my kids love it...!
Very good place for kids and sea water view. Not real sea with waves but neat and clean sitting place on park to see the water.

What I like about this park is that it's divided into several sections, each with a different atmosphere. If you've got a family and have a hankering for fast food and kiddie swings, go to the main/central section. If however you're like me and wish to avoid noisy kids and their sometimes even noisier parents, the section near the dog run is far more tranquil (with the exception of the endless string of container trucks rumbling past, and the monotonous, mind numbing beeping coming from the adjacent container terminal). I fully expect that West Coast Park will lose its personality when it's incorporated into the Greater Southern Waterfront plans, but unfortunately this is Singapore, and nothing here remains unchanged for long.
A calm and serene place for a evening stroll.
Best place to let kids release their energy and have a great meal at the McDonald's. Playground, cycling, kite flying, fast food. Enough shades to cool off during the days.
Nice dog park in the city. Ample space and very well-maintained.
Good place to relax.
Nice and quiet, with enough park for a walk. There is a playground area too near the McDonald's. Good outing for the kids.

Fabulous spot for children of any age. I‚Äôd suggest long pants for the slides do heat up.

Great selection of equipment for all ages.

This park is a favourite for kids but the car park is now chargeable.
Kids love this place. Less crowd, easy parking, big playground and good for picnic under shady trees.

Unique experience for young and old;playground elements that you hardly find in your HDB ones,great ocean views where the small boats sails , pebble bed for that relaxing message, fitness run trail to next park if you like, board walk above swamp areas at the side, bus stop right in front of park, good car parking space as well, definitely a fave üòÄ
Still one of my fav place in the west to bring the kids to have fun ü§ü
Lots of kids play areas with many themes.

Not as well known as ECP but shady and, of course, smaller. From the dog park in the South, to the wetlands boardwalks to the north, it is a great exercise and picnic spot. Maybe some would be put off with the noise of endless trucks at the port, but they're easy to ignore
Nice place for kids to play, walking jogging and relaxation.
Nice place for a Family get together
One of the best playground in SIngapore. Big space for children to run around and play different types of theme.

One of the really nice things about living in the Garden City is access to these sprawling stretches of green carved out for biking, running, skating and general frolicking.  Facilities include big playgrounds with zip lines, enormous jungle gyms, and climbing frames for kids.   The breeze here is not always consistent so kite flying might be a sometime thing.   McDonald's has craftily situated a very big outlet here where birthday parties can be hosted.    A big park, not as big as East Coast park, but certainly a lot less crowded.
A great place to relax on holidays
One of my favourite places to come and soak in some sea air. Might not be as picturesque as some of the other beaches in Singapore but its peaceful on a week day.

This park consists of 2 portions, seperated by Clementi Road. The west wing seems to be more alive than the east wing of the park. However, both sides also have toilets with shower facilities. The McDonald's is located at the west wing, which also attracts more families with young children to the west wing as well. Weekends can get really crowded but weekdays are fine.

Awesome place to cycle. There's a bicycle rental shop (GoCycling) here too which has both bicycles (varying sizes=varying prices) and go carts. Would recommend you bring your own food though cos the McDonald's is usually very full. Ready availability of canned and bottles drinks as there are vending machines all over the park.

Love the open space for the dogs. However can be further improved. The fence is a bit low and dogs that can jump will definitely be able to jump out easily. Then the back area is super under utilised. Used to be part of the dog park but then after renovation the dog park shrink by half.

Great place to go to enjoy the outdoors. Go for a run. Climb the play structures. Enjoy the sunset. Get out camping. Have a BBQ. Explore the boardwalks and get a glimpse at mangroves. Grab a bite at the newly renovated MacDonalds. It's a great place to rewind for a bit.
Quite a big park for children in to play around. It has an overlooking sea front, though not that wide but offer a good sunset view on a good day.
Parking fee $1.20 per hour

Although this is free national park, kids can enjoy staying here for sure!
It has several play ground, sand park, green, athletics, Gymnastics, bicycle rental shop, all option you can choose.
Especially Long slide in this park is bit challenging for small kids, parents need to be accompanied with.
Great place for family activities such as picnic, Frisbee and letting the kids explore the playground. But cycling in the park is pretty boring as you can cover the park in less than half an hour.
Great Park, balanced crowd, nice folks, wonderful to exercise, bring the kids for some cycling, scooting, roller blading and skating too! Jogging is a mainstay with most here.
This park is very nice place and I'm very enjoy...

Nice big open space, for all age groups to enjoy. Adults flying kites, kids at the playground or sand pit and others chilling out under shady trees

Not much of a beach. Good for fishing, side views, sports, playgrounds and kite flying I guess. A little scary on the forest side. Quite small, quite numbers of shelters only and only has McDonald. Will be good if there will be more sitting area, food place & more leissure.

West Coast Park is, well, a park. The best thing about it is that it is the place-of-choice for many beautiful families ‚Ä?some, three-generational ‚Ä?that spend their time in every way that a park could possibly afford, such as, picnicking, cycling, frisbee-ing; you name it, and you'll find it there. Amazing park at the west coast of Singapore. Key attractions are beach volleyball courts, baseball fields, camping sites and the cycling trails. It's a good place to spend the weekend with family.
Nicest place to chill and workout in the western part of Singapore
Made friends with the chickens there, had them for dinner!
Wow really piece full place I really like that place besides sea bot's .

Nice place to run, walk, play ball games. Amenities include: washrooms, camping site, jetties and nearby bird sanctuary. There is a dog park on the other side of the park. Playgrounds for pre school kids as well as older kids.
good for family outdoor activities

Only park where you can stare at the sea in the industrial west, and when you look out into the sea, you'll see docks and shipyards ü§£ It's not huge, just about 5km one loop. There's a 24hrs (before COVID) McDonald's, but there's no free parking in all it's 3 carparks. But it's not usually packed as well (especially the eastern loop where you can stare at container cranes), which is why I love it so much.
Very nice park.kids loves it. We can tent day and night and do fishing too.

Very peaceful place because it is not as crowded as other more popular parks in Singapore. Well, on most weekdays anyway.

This place is good for nature lovers, joggers or strollers and anyone who just want to enjoy the greeneries, lusting at the boats docked at the marina or the sea.

There is a playing area for small children, a fast food restaurant and a shop to rent bicycles.

I tried fishing a few times at different stretch of the beach but the results were always disappointing. Never tried swimming here though.

Ample car parking lots but can get very crowded on weekends.
Park is nice specially the play area near park area 3. But the barbecue pits (park area 2) do not face the water. Overall a good space for picnic and easily accessible by bus 175 and 176.
West coast park is 3km long with PCN road. It is good for cycling and skating. We can see nice harbour view from there  and there are many children playground area around the park.
Love this place. You could enjoy nature, kids run in the playground or even busk in the sun. A place for all ages.
Quiet park, a loop in the park takes up 8km, sea view, flowers, squirrels, monitor lizard, fishes, paid parking, came here for breakfast at McDonald before my walk.

A great place in the West to go for a jog or cycling. Not overly crowded most of the time.  Good size car park. There's a great outdoor playground for the kids that are constantly upgrading. There's McDonald and mccafe in the park.  Dogs lover can bring your dogs to the dog run located at the end of the park.  Nearby there's a lot of nice food too. Nearest shopping at West Coast Plaza.

As a family, we sometimes walk to the park, with our 2 kids bringing their bikes. The paths are well maintained, there's lots of space for pedestrians and cyclists to share the space.

There is a place to hire bikes and gokarts, too.

There are a couple of good play areas, with one of them catering for younger children. There is a pedestrian only walk around the marsh area and you often get to bump into wildlife (not literally).

Some people pitch up tents and camp. Others hire BBQ areas.

If you're hungry or thirst, there is a good sized Macdonalds. Given the size of the park, this is the only food outlet.

A great park.
West coast park is a nice place for family to relax. Have children play ground for children to have fun. Also can do fishing for those fishing kakis.
Could use more restaurants in the area
Nice playgrounds for kids. Nothing to see on the beach etc - there is no beach actually. Very noisy due to next door port. Goto East Coast instead.
nice place to sight seeing
A good place to chill by the sea. No beach but I love how the pavement made close to the shore. View at night is great looking across the shore.
A gem of parks in singapore. Great weather helps when exploring the location.

Great open spaces and various playgrounds for kids of all ages. Nice view of the sea too. McDonald's conveniently located in the vicinity for a quick bite for the kids. Lots of trees for shade as well.

Was there for the BBQ company gathering. It feels safe and within stone throw distance to bike rental shop & toilet. It is a park next to the export port. It looks interesting to me, very eager to fly a drone there!

Not much to do. Just a regular park by the sea. Huge play areas, great for picnics. Good place to bring pets and kids. There is a pet wash located in the front. Bbq pits all round, good carpark space. 24 hour mcdonalds with drive thru. Park is open to public all day. Joggers can be seen day and night. Toilet is open and clean to a certain extent.
I love the place . Walking everyday. Good exercise everyday..fresh air greeny..i enjoy it

Nice place to take a morning or evening run, wether it's during the weekdays or the weekend. It does get more crowded during the weekends, but that's because there are playgrounds and BBQ pits where families and friends can gather to enjoy a pleasant day.
the ambience was good specially not crowded..thank you singapore for that place..üòòüòò

It's a good park to be out and about with the kids. Not as developed or big as ECP but holds its own nevertheless. Great place to let your (mobile-age) kids burn off some energy.
Be warned, the great enemy of this cause - MacDonalds - has about the *only* F&B presence in line-of-sight

Wide open space for kids to run around. With the many trees and tall buildings in Singapore, this is also one of the good spots for kite flying. Spacious park with many playgrounds suitable for children of various ages. Good place for play dates. My 1.5 year old niece loved the baby swing.
A great place for kids to expend some energy. Fantastic play equipment, great views over the sea and nearby restaurants make this a fun place to spend an afternoon.

This McDonald is at the West Coast Park and is near the Park Children playground. Naturally, it becomes a regular haunt for parents and NUS students. It has both air-conditioned in door seats, as well as outdoor non air conditioned seating areas.

The story book is really nice as a happy meal toy.
Thanks MacDonald for giving us good environment,they just renovated their west coast branch.
The playground is fun and there is a large field for you to play whatever you want, like football, kite flying and maybe even drive your drone or remote control car

Place to hang out with family/group.
But un fortunately no good beach
Very nice place, lot of playgrounds for kids to enjoy specially the zipline, lot of free space to play around. Comparatively less crowded, another best thing during safe distancing measures üòÄ
Nice running route but too noisy from the constructions around and shipping ports. Clean toilet, many playgrounds, good place for the family or just to chill after a long day.

Very nice track for cycling. There is a bicycle rent shop as well.
The entire track to and fro is almost 6km

More so than the  beach  it is garden. You can spend some quiet time if you are lucky  and not many people around. The place  has only.one Mc Donald's  and Mc caffe if you wanna  grab a coffee or a burger.   As i saw you can book camp sites as well. Overall nice place

If you have both seniors and kids and you cant decide where to go, here's the ultimate place. For seniors, there is a 5.2km loop if they want a nice stroll in the park.
For kids, there a massive playground with obstacle courses for all ages, a pyrimid, a flying fox and just a regular playground. Do be warned that at the obstacle courses, pyrimads and flying foxes, the flooring is all sand. You can bring some food along with a picnic blanket and have a picinic in the park. The scenery is lovely. What happens if you run out of food? Don't worry. There is a MacDonalds right in the middle of the park. If you are skateboarding. Around the playground is good but if you are cycling, try out the 5.2km loop. The west coast underpass is a steep downhill followed by a steep uphill. What happens if you forgot to bring your bicycle and really really want to cycle? Well the solution is simple. There is a bike rental shop. There are three carparks, wheelchair parking and wheelchair accesible entrance.
Nice to Do exercise like jogging
Lots of different play areas and looked nice and clean!

west is not as beautiful as the east. of singapore, i mean. i am on my √©pic'2 day cycling journey through the whole circumference of this island.

west coast park nevertheless has very healthy mature trees thriving in all the greenery glory. is it the harsh air that makes the plants grow better?
lots of kite flying and of course the famous Mcdonalds in the park.
